#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:3 ../../algorithms/sac.rst:83
msgid "Soft Actor-Critic"
msgstr "軟性演員-評論家 (Soft Actor-Critic)"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:5
msgid "Table of Contents"
msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:8
msgid "Background"
msgstr "背景"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:10
msgid "(Previously: `Background for TD3`_)"
msgstr "（先前章節：`Background for TD3`_）"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:14
msgid ""
"Soft Actor Critic (SAC) is an algorithm that optimizes a stochastic "
"policy in an off-policy way, forming a bridge between stochastic policy "
"optimization and DDPG-style approaches. It isn't a direct successor to "
"TD3 (having been published roughly concurrently), but it incorporates the"
" clipped double-Q trick, and due to the inherent stochasticity of the "
"policy in SAC, it also winds up benefiting from something like target "
"policy smoothing."
msgstr ""
"軟性演員-評論家 (SAC) 是一種以離策略 (Off-policy) 方式優化隨機策略 "
"(Stochastic Policy) 的演算法，在隨機策略優化和 DDPG 風格方法之間架起了橋樑。"
"它並非 TD3 的直接後繼者（兩者幾乎同時發表），但它採用了截斷雙 Q (Clipped "
"Double-Q) 技巧，且由於 SAC 中策略固有的隨機性，它也從類似目標策略平滑化 "
"(Target Policy Smoothing) 的效果中獲益。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:16
msgid ""
"A central feature of SAC is **entropy regularization.** The policy is "
"trained to maximize a trade-off between expected return and `entropy`_, a"
" measure of randomness in the policy. This has a close connection to the "
"exploration-exploitation trade-off: increasing entropy results in more "
"exploration, which can accelerate learning later on. It can also prevent "
"the policy from prematurely converging to a bad local optimum."
msgstr ""
"SAC 的核心特徵是**熵正則化 (Entropy Regularization)**。策略被訓練為最大化期望"
"回報 (Return) 與 `entropy`_（熵，一種衡量策略隨機性的度量）之間的權衡。這與探"
"索-利用權衡密切相關：增加熵會帶來更多探索 (Exploration)，這可以加速後續學習。"
"它也可以防止策略過早收斂到不好的局部最優解 (Local Optima)。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:21
msgid "Quick Facts"
msgstr "快速概覽"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:23
msgid "SAC is an off-policy algorithm."
msgstr "SAC 是一種離策略演算法。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:24
msgid ""
"The version of SAC implemented here can only be used for environments "
"with continuous action spaces."
msgstr "此處實作的 SAC 版本只能用於具有連續動作空間 (Action Space) 的環境。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:25
msgid ""
"An alternate version of SAC, which slightly changes the policy update "
"rule, can be implemented to handle discrete action spaces."
msgstr "SAC 的另一個版本稍微修改了策略更新規則，可以用來處理離散動作空間。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:26
msgid "The Spinning Up implementation of SAC does not support parallelization."
msgstr "Spinning Up 的 SAC 實作不支援平行化。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:29
msgid "Key Equations"
msgstr "關鍵方程式"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:31
msgid ""
"To explain Soft Actor Critic, we first have to introduce the entropy-"
"regularized reinforcement learning setting. In entropy-regularized RL, "
"there are slightly-different equations for value functions."
msgstr ""
"為了解釋軟性演員-評論家，我們首先需要介紹熵正則化強化學習的設定。在熵正則化強"
"化學習中，價值函數 (Value Function) 的方程式略有不同。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:34
msgid "Entropy-Regularized Reinforcement Learning"
msgstr "熵正則化強化學習"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:36
msgid ""
"Entropy is a quantity which, roughly speaking, says how random a random "
"variable is. If a coin is weighted so that it almost always comes up "
"heads, it has low entropy; if it's evenly weighted and has a half chance "
"of either outcome, it has high entropy."
msgstr ""
"熵是一個量，粗略地說，它衡量一個隨機變數的隨機程度。如果一枚硬幣的權重使其幾"
"乎總是出現正面，它的熵就很低；如果它是均勻加權的，兩種結果各有一半的機會，它"
"的熵就很高。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:38
msgid ""
"Let :math:`x` be a random variable with probability mass or density "
"function :math:`P`. The entropy :math:`H` of :math:`x` is computed from "
"its distribution :math:`P` according to"
msgstr ""
"令 :math:`x` 為具有機率質量函數或密度函數 :math:`P` 的隨機變數。:math:`x` 的"
"熵 :math:`H` 由其分佈 :math:`P` 按以下方式計算"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:40
#, python-brace-format
msgid "H(P) = \\underE{x \\sim P}{-\\log P(x)}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:44
msgid ""
"In entropy-regularized reinforcement learning, the agent gets a bonus "
"reward at each time step proportional to the entropy of the policy at "
"that timestep. This changes `the RL problem`_ to:"
msgstr ""
"在熵正則化強化學習中，代理程式在每個時間步獲得與該時間步策略熵成正比的額外獎"
"勵。這將 `the RL problem`_ 改變為："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:46
msgid ""
"\\pi^* = \\arg \\max_{\\pi} \\underE{\\tau \\sim \\pi}{ "
"\\sum_{t=0}^{\\infty} \\gamma^t \\bigg( R(s_t, a_t, s_{t+1}) + \\alpha "
"H\\left(\\pi(\\cdot|s_t)\\right) \\bigg)},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:50
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\alpha > 0` is the trade-off coefficient. (Note: we're "
"assuming an infinite-horizon discounted setting here, and we'll do the "
"same for the rest of this page.) We can now define the slightly-different"
" value functions in this setting. :math:`V^{\\pi}` is changed to include "
"the entropy bonuses from every timestep:"
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`\\alpha > 0` 是權衡係數。（注意：我們在此假設無限時域折扣設定，本"
"頁其餘部分也將如此。）我們現在可以定義此設定中略有不同的價值函數。"
":math:`V^{\\pi}` 被修改為包含每個時間步的熵獎勵："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:52
msgid ""
"V^{\\pi}(s) = \\underE{\\tau \\sim \\pi}{ \\left. \\sum_{t=0}^{\\infty} "
"\\gamma^t \\bigg( R(s_t, a_t, s_{t+1}) + \\alpha "
"H\\left(\\pi(\\cdot|s_t)\\right) \\bigg) \\right| s_0 = s}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:56
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
":math:`Q^{\\pi}` is changed to include the entropy bonuses from every "
"timestep *except the first*:"
msgstr ":math:`Q^{\\pi}` 被修改為包含*除第一個時間步以外*每個時間步的熵獎勵："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:58
msgid ""
"Q^{\\pi}(s,a) = \\underE{\\tau \\sim \\pi}{ \\left. \\sum_{t=0}^{\\infty}"
" \\gamma^t  R(s_t, a_t, s_{t+1}) + \\alpha \\sum_{t=1}^{\\infty} "
"\\gamma^t H\\left(\\pi(\\cdot|s_t)\\right)\\right| s_0 = s, a_0 = a}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:62
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"With these definitions, :math:`V^{\\pi}` and :math:`Q^{\\pi}` are "
"connected by:"
msgstr "根據這些定義，:math:`V^{\\pi}` 和 :math:`Q^{\\pi}` 的關係為："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:64
msgid ""
"V^{\\pi}(s) = \\underE{a \\sim \\pi}{Q^{\\pi}(s,a)} + \\alpha "
"H\\left(\\pi(\\cdot|s)\\right)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:68
#, python-brace-format
msgid "and the Bellman equation for :math:`Q^{\\pi}` is"
msgstr "而 :math:`Q^{\\pi}` 的 Bellman 方程式為"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:70
msgid ""
"Q^{\\pi}(s,a) &= \\underE{s' \\sim P \\\\ a' \\sim \\pi}{R(s,a,s') + "
"\\gamma\\left(Q^{\\pi}(s',a') + \\alpha H\\left(\\pi(\\cdot|s')\\right) "
"\\right)} \\\\\n"
"&= \\underE{s' \\sim P}{R(s,a,s') + \\gamma V^{\\pi}(s')}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:77 ../../algorithms/sac.rst:87
#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:124 ../../algorithms/sac.rst:158
#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:188 ../../algorithms/sac.rst:242
msgid "You Should Know"
msgstr "你應該知道"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:79
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The way we've set up the value functions in the entropy-regularized "
"setting is a little bit arbitrary, and actually we could have done it "
"differently (eg make :math:`Q^{\\pi}` include the entropy bonus at the "
"first timestep). The choice of definition may vary slightly across papers"
" on the subject."
msgstr ""
"我們在熵正則化設定中建立價值函數的方式有點隨意，實際上我們可以用不同的方式"
"（例如讓 :math:`Q^{\\pi}` 包含第一個時間步的熵獎勵）。定義的選擇在相關論文中"
"可能略有不同。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:85
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"SAC concurrently learns a policy :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}` and two "
"Q-functions :math:`Q_{\\phi_1}, Q_{\\phi_2}`. There are two variants of "
"SAC that are currently standard: one that uses a fixed entropy "
"regularization coefficient :math:`\\alpha`, and another that enforces an "
"entropy constraint by varying :math:`\\alpha` over the course of "
"training. For simplicity, Spinning Up makes use of the version with a "
"fixed entropy regularization coefficient, but the entropy-constrained "
"variant is generally preferred by practitioners."
msgstr ""
"SAC 同時學習一個策略 :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}` 和兩個 Q 函數 "
":math:`Q_{\\phi_1}, Q_{\\phi_2}`。SAC 目前有兩個標準變體：一個使用固定的熵正"
"則化係數 :math:`\\alpha`，另一個透過在訓練過程中調整 :math:`\\alpha` 來施加熵"
"約束。為了簡單起見，Spinning Up 使用固定熵正則化係數的版本，但實務工作者通常"
"偏好熵約束版本。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:89
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The SAC algorithm has changed a little bit over time. An older version of"
" SAC also learns a value function :math:`V_{\\psi}` in addition to the "
"Q-functions; this page will focus on the modern version that omits the "
"extra value function."
msgstr ""
"SAC 演算法隨時間有了些微變化。較早版本的 SAC 除了 Q 函數外還學習一個價值函"
"數 :math:`V_{\\psi}`；本頁將聚焦於省略額外價值函數的現代版本。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:93
msgid ""
"**Learning Q.** The Q-functions are learned in a similar way to TD3, but "
"with a few key differences."
msgstr ""
"**學習 Q。** Q 函數的學習方式與 TD3 類似，但有幾個關鍵差異。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:95
msgid "First, what's similar?"
msgstr "首先，有什麼相似之處？"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:97
msgid ""
"Like in TD3, both Q-functions are learned with MSBE minimization, by "
"regressing to a single shared target."
msgstr "與 TD3 相同，兩個 Q 函數都透過回歸到單一共享目標值，以 MSBE 最小化來學習。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:99
msgid ""
"Like in TD3, the shared target is computed using target Q-networks, and "
"the target Q-networks are obtained by polyak averaging the Q-network "
"parameters over the course of training."
msgstr ""
"與 TD3 相同，共享目標值使用目標 Q 網路 (Target Network) 計算，目標 Q 網路透過"
"在訓練過程中對 Q 網路參數進行 Polyak 平均來獲得。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:101
msgid ""
"Like in TD3, the shared target makes use of the **clipped double-Q** "
"trick."
msgstr "與 TD3 相同，共享目標值使用了**截斷雙 Q** 技巧。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:103
msgid "What's different?"
msgstr "有什麼不同之處？"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:105
msgid ""
"Unlike in TD3, the target also includes a term that comes from SAC's use "
"of entropy regularization."
msgstr "與 TD3 不同的是，目標值還包含一個來自 SAC 使用熵正則化的項。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:107
msgid ""
"Unlike in TD3, the next-state actions used in the target come from the "
"**current policy** instead of a target policy."
msgstr "與 TD3 不同的是，目標值中使用的下一狀態動作來自**當前策略**而非目標策略。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:109
msgid ""
"Unlike in TD3, there is no explicit target policy smoothing. TD3 trains a"
" deterministic policy, and so it accomplishes smoothing by adding random "
"noise to the next-state actions. SAC trains a stochastic policy, and so "
"the noise from that stochasticity is sufficient to get a similar effect."
msgstr ""
"與 TD3 不同的是，沒有明確的目標策略平滑化。TD3 訓練的是確定性策略，因此透過向"
"下一狀態動作添加隨機雜訊來實現平滑化。SAC 訓練的是隨機策略，因此來自隨機性的"
"雜訊已足以產生類似效果。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:111
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Before we give the final form of the Q-loss, let's take a moment to "
"discuss how the contribution from entropy regularization comes in. We'll "
"start by taking our recursive Bellman equation for the entropy-"
"regularized :math:`Q^{\\pi}` from earlier, and rewriting it a little bit "
"by using the definition of entropy:"
msgstr ""
"在給出 Q 損失的最終形式之前，讓我們花點時間討論熵正則化的貢獻是如何產生的。我"
"們從之前的熵正則化 :math:`Q^{\\pi}` 的遞迴 Bellman 方程式開始，利用熵的定義"
"稍加改寫："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:113
msgid ""
"Q^{\\pi}(s,a) &= \\underE{s' \\sim P \\\\ a' \\sim \\pi}{R(s,a,s') + "
"\\gamma\\left(Q^{\\pi}(s',a') + \\alpha H\\left(\\pi(\\cdot|s')\\right) "
"\\right)} \\\\\n"
"&= \\underE{s' \\sim P \\\\ a' \\sim \\pi}{R(s,a,s') + "
"\\gamma\\left(Q^{\\pi}(s',a') - \\alpha \\log \\pi(a'|s') \\right)}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:118
msgid ""
"The RHS is an expectation over next states (which come from the replay "
"buffer) and next actions (which come from the current policy, and **not**"
" the replay buffer). Since it's an expectation, we can approximate it "
"with samples:"
msgstr ""
"右側是對下一狀態（來自經驗回放緩衝區 (Replay Buffer)）和下一動作（來自當前策"
"略，而**不是**回放緩衝區）的期望。由於它是一個期望值，我們可以用取樣來近似它："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:120
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Q^{\\pi}(s,a) &\\approx r + \\gamma\\left(Q^{\\pi}(s',\\tilde{a}') - "
"\\alpha \\log \\pi(\\tilde{a}'|s') \\right), \\;\\;\\;\\;\\;  \\tilde{a}'"
" \\sim \\pi(\\cdot|s')."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:126
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"We switch next action notation to :math:`\\tilde{a}'`, instead of "
":math:`a'`, to highlight that the next actions have to be sampled fresh "
"from the policy (whereas by contrast, :math:`r` and :math:`s'` should "
"come from the replay buffer)."
msgstr ""
"我們將下一動作的符號改為 :math:`\\tilde{a}'` 而非 :math:`a'`，以強調下一動作"
"必須從策略中重新取樣（相比之下，:math:`r` 和 :math:`s'` 應來自回放緩衝區）。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:128
msgid ""
"SAC sets up the MSBE loss for each Q-function using this kind of sample "
"approximation for the target. The only thing still undetermined here is "
"which Q-function gets used to compute the sample backup: like TD3, SAC "
"uses the clipped double-Q trick, and takes the minimum Q-value between "
"the two Q approximators."
msgstr ""
"SAC 使用這種取樣近似來為每個 Q 函數建立 MSBE 損失。唯一尚未確定的是使用哪個 "
"Q 函數來計算取樣備份值：與 TD3 一樣，SAC 使用截斷雙 Q 技巧，取兩個 Q 近似器"
"中較小的 Q 值。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:130
msgid "Putting it all together, the loss functions for the Q-networks in SAC are:"
msgstr "綜合以上所有內容，SAC 中 Q 網路的損失函數為："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:132
msgid ""
"L(\\phi_i, {\\mathcal D}) = \\underset{(s,a,r,s',d) \\sim {\\mathcal "
"D}}{{\\mathrm E}}\\left[\n"
"    \\Bigg( Q_{\\phi_i}(s,a) - y(r,s',d) \\Bigg)^2\n"
"    \\right],"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:138
msgid "where the target is given by"
msgstr "其中目標值定義為"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:140
msgid ""
"y(r, s', d) = r + \\gamma (1 - d) \\left( \\min_{j=1,2} "
"Q_{\\phi_{\\text{targ},j}}(s', \\tilde{a}') - \\alpha \\log "
"\\pi_{\\theta}(\\tilde{a}'|s') \\right), \\;\\;\\;\\;\\; \\tilde{a}' "
"\\sim \\pi_{\\theta}(\\cdot|s')."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:145
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**Learning the Policy.** The policy should, in each state, act to "
"maximize the expected future return plus expected future entropy. That "
"is, it should maximize :math:`V^{\\pi}(s)`, which we expand out into"
msgstr ""
"**學習策略。** 策略在每個狀態下，應該以最大化期望未來回報加期望未來熵的方式行"
"動。也就是說，它應該最大化 :math:`V^{\\pi}(s)`，我們將其展開為"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:147
msgid ""
"V^{\\pi}(s) &= \\underE{a \\sim \\pi}{Q^{\\pi}(s,a)} + \\alpha "
"H\\left(\\pi(\\cdot|s)\\right) \\\\\n"
"&= \\underE{a \\sim \\pi}{Q^{\\pi}(s,a) - \\alpha \\log \\pi(a|s)}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:152
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The way we optimize the policy makes use of the **reparameterization "
"trick**, in which a sample from :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(\\cdot|s)` is drawn"
" by computing a deterministic function of state, policy parameters, and "
"independent noise. To illustrate: following the authors of the SAC paper,"
" we use a squashed Gaussian policy, which means that samples are obtained"
" according to"
msgstr ""
"我們優化策略的方式利用了**重參數化技巧 (Reparameterization Trick)**，其中從 "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(\\cdot|s)` 取樣是透過計算狀態、策略參數和獨立雜訊的確定"
"性函數來完成的。為說明這一點：按照 SAC 論文作者的做法，我們使用壓縮高斯策略"
" (Squashed Gaussian Policy)，這意味著取樣按以下方式獲得"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:154
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\tilde{a}_{\\theta}(s, \\xi) = \\tanh\\left( \\mu_{\\theta}(s) + "
"\\sigma_{\\theta}(s) \\odot \\xi \\right), \\;\\;\\;\\;\\; \\xi \\sim "
"\\mathcal{N}(0, I)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:160
msgid ""
"This policy has two key differences from the policies we use in the other"
" policy optimization algorithms:"
msgstr "此策略與我們在其他策略優化演算法中使用的策略有兩個關鍵差異："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:162
msgid ""
"**1. The squashing function.** The :math:`\\tanh` in the SAC policy "
"ensures that actions are bounded to a finite range. This is absent in the"
" VPG, TRPO, and PPO policies. It also changes the distribution: before "
"the :math:`\\tanh` the SAC policy is a factored Gaussian like the other "
"algorithms' policies, but after the :math:`\\tanh` it is not. (You can "
"still compute the log-probabilities of actions in closed form, though: "
"see the paper appendix for details.)"
msgstr ""
"**1. 壓縮函數。** SAC 策略中的 :math:`\\tanh` 確保動作被限定在有限範圍內。這"
"在 VPG、TRPO 和 PPO 策略中不存在。它也改變了分佈：在 :math:`\\tanh` 之前，"
"SAC 策略是一個與其他演算法策略相同的分解高斯分佈，但在 :math:`\\tanh` 之後就"
"不是了。（不過，你仍然可以用封閉形式計算動作的對數機率：詳見論文附錄。）"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:164
msgid ""
"**2. The way standard deviations are parameterized.** In VPG, TRPO, and "
"PPO, we represent the log std devs with state-independent parameter "
"vectors. In SAC, we represent the log std devs as outputs from the neural"
" network, meaning that they depend on state in a complex way. SAC with "
"state-independent log std devs, in our experience, did not work. (Can you"
" think of why? Or better yet: run an experiment to verify?)"
msgstr ""
"**2. 標準差的參數化方式。** 在 VPG、TRPO 和 PPO 中，我們用與狀態無關的參數向"
"量來表示對數標準差。在 SAC 中，我們將對數標準差表示為神經網路的輸出，這意味著"
"它們以複雜的方式依賴於狀態。根據我們的經驗，使用與狀態無關的對數標準差的 SAC "
"無法正常運作。（你能想到為什麼嗎？或者更好的是：執行一個實驗來驗證？）"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:166
msgid ""
"The reparameterization trick allows us to rewrite the expectation over "
"actions (which contains a pain point: the distribution depends on the "
"policy parameters) into an expectation over noise (which removes the pain"
" point: the distribution now has no dependence on parameters):"
msgstr ""
"重參數化技巧讓我們能夠將對動作的期望（其中有一個痛點：分佈依賴於策略參數）改"
"寫為對雜訊的期望（這消除了痛點：分佈現在不再依賴於參數）："

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:168
msgid ""
"\\underE{a \\sim \\pi_{\\theta}}{Q^{\\pi_{\\theta}}(s,a) - \\alpha \\log "
"\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)} = \\underE{\\xi \\sim "
"\\mathcal{N}}{Q^{\\pi_{\\theta}}(s,\\tilde{a}_{\\theta}(s,\\xi)) - "
"\\alpha \\log \\pi_{\\theta}(\\tilde{a}_{\\theta}(s,\\xi)|s)}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:172
msgid ""
"To get the policy loss, the final step is that we need to substitute "
":math:`Q^{\\pi_{\\theta}}` with one of our function approximators. Unlike"
" in TD3, which uses :math:`Q_{\\phi_1}` (just the first Q approximator), "
"SAC uses :math:`\\min_{j=1,2} Q_{\\phi_j}` (the minimum of the two Q "
"approximators). The policy is thus optimized according to"
msgstr ""
"要得到策略損失，最後一步是我們需要用函數近似器之一替換 "
":math:`Q^{\\pi_{\\theta}}`。與 TD3 使用 :math:`Q_{\\phi_1}`（僅第一個 Q 近似"
"器）不同，SAC 使用 :math:`\\min_{j=1,2} Q_{\\phi_j}`（兩個 Q 近似器中的最小"
"值）。策略因此按以下方式優化"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:174
msgid ""
"\\max_{\\theta} \\underE{s \\sim \\mathcal{D} \\\\ \\xi \\sim "
"\\mathcal{N}}{\\min_{j=1,2} Q_{\\phi_j}(s,\\tilde{a}_{\\theta}(s,\\xi)) -"
" \\alpha \\log \\pi_{\\theta}(\\tilde{a}_{\\theta}(s,\\xi)|s)},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:178
msgid ""
"which is almost the same as the DDPG and TD3 policy optimization, except "
"for the min-double-Q trick, the stochasticity, and the entropy term."
msgstr ""
"這與 DDPG 和 TD3 的策略優化幾乎相同，除了最小雙 Q 技巧、隨機性和熵項。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:182
msgid "Exploration vs. Exploitation"
msgstr "探索與利用"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:184
msgid ""
"SAC trains a stochastic policy with entropy regularization, and explores "
"in an on-policy way. The entropy regularization coefficient "
":math:`\\alpha` explicitly controls the explore-exploit tradeoff, with "
"higher :math:`\\alpha` corresponding to more exploration, and lower "
":math:`\\alpha` corresponding to more exploitation. The right coefficient"
" (the one which leads to the stablest / highest-reward learning) may vary"
" from environment to environment, and could require careful tuning."
msgstr ""
"SAC 透過熵正則化訓練一個隨機策略，並以同策略的方式進行探索。熵正則化係數 "
":math:`\\alpha` 明確控制探索-利用 (Exploitation) 權衡，較高的 :math:`\\alpha` "
"對應更多探索，較低的 :math:`\\alpha` 對應更多利用。合適的係數（能帶來最穩定/"
"最高獎勵學習的那個）可能因環境而異，可能需要仔細調整。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:186
msgid ""
"At test time, to see how well the policy exploits what it has learned, we"
" remove stochasticity and use the mean action instead of a sample from "
"the distribution. This tends to improve performance over the original "
"stochastic policy."
msgstr ""
"在測試時，為了觀察策略如何利用所學到的知識，我們移除隨機性並使用均值動作而非"
"從分佈中取樣。這通常比原始隨機策略表現更好。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:190
msgid ""
"Our SAC implementation uses a trick to improve exploration at the start "
"of training. For a fixed number of steps at the beginning (set with the "
"``start_steps`` keyword argument), the agent takes actions which are "
"sampled from a uniform random distribution over valid actions. After "
"that, it returns to normal SAC exploration."
msgstr ""
"我們的 SAC 實作使用了一個技巧來改善訓練初期的探索。在開始的固定步數內（透過"
" ``start_steps`` 關鍵字引數設定），代理程式從有效動作的均勻隨機分佈中取樣動"
"作。之後，它恢復到正常的 SAC 探索方式。"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:194
msgid "Pseudocode"
msgstr "虛擬碼"

#: ../../algorithms/sac.rst:197
msgid ""
"\\begin{algorithm}[H]\n"
"    \\caption{Soft Actor-Critic}\n"
"    \\label{alg1}\n"
"\\begin{algorithmic}[1]\n"
"    \\STATE Input: initial policy parameters $\\theta$, Q-function "
"parameters $\\phi_1$, $\\phi_2$, empty replay buffer $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"    \\STATE Set target parameters equal to main parameters "
"$\\phi_{\\text{targ},1} \\leftarrow \\phi_1$, $\\phi_{\\text{targ},2} "
"\\leftarrow \\phi_2$\n"
"    \\REPEAT\n"
"        \\STATE Observe state $s$ and select action $a \\sim "
"\\pi_{\\theta}(\\cdot|s)$\n"
"        \\STATE Execute $a$ in the environment\n"
"        \\STATE Observe next state $s'$, reward $r$, and done signal $d$ "
"to indicate whether $s'$ is terminal\n"
"        \\STATE Store $(s,a,r,s',d)$ in replay buffer $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"        \\STATE If $s'$ is terminal, reset environment state.\n"
"        \\IF{it's time to update}\n"
"            \\FOR{$j$ in range(however many updates)}\n"
"                \\STATE Randomly sample a batch of transitions, $B = \\{ "
"(s,a,r,s',d) \\}$ from $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"                \\STATE Compute targets for the Q functions:\n"
"                \\begin{align*}\n"
"                    y (r,s',d) &= r + \\gamma (1-d) \\left(\\min_{i=1,2} "
"Q_{\\phi_{\\text{targ}, i}} (s', \\tilde{a}') - \\alpha \\log "
"\\pi_{\\theta}(\\tilde{a}'|s')\\right), && \\tilde{a}' \\sim "
"\\pi_{\\theta}(\\cdot|s')\n"
"                \\end{align*}\n"
"                \\STATE Update Q-functions by one step of gradient "
"descent using\n"
"                \\begin{align*}\n"
"                    & \\nabla_{\\phi_i} \\frac{1}{|B|}\\sum_{(s,a,r,s',d)"
" \\in B} \\left( Q_{\\phi_i}(s,a) - y(r,s',d) \\right)^2 && \\text{for } "
"i=1,2\n"
"                \\end{align*}\n"
"                \\STATE Update policy by one step of gradient ascent "
"using\n"
"                \\begin{equation*}\n"
"                    \\nabla_{\\theta} \\frac{1}{|B|}\\sum_{s \\in B} "
"\\Big(\\min_{i=1,2} Q_{\\phi_i}(s, \\tilde{a}_{\\theta}(s)) - \\alpha "
"\\log \\pi_{\\theta} \\left(\\left. \\tilde{a}_{\\theta}(s) \\right| "
"s\\right) \\Big),\n"
"                \\end{equation*}\n"
"                where $\\tilde{a}_{\\theta}(s)$ is a sample from "
"$\\pi_{\\theta}(\\cdot|s)$ which is differentiable wrt $\\theta$ via the "
"reparametrization trick.\n"
"                \\STATE Update target networks with\n"
"                \\begin{align*}\n"
"                    \\phi_{\\text{targ},i} &\\leftarrow \\rho "
"\\phi_{\\text{targ}, i} + (1-\\rho) \\phi_i && \\text{for } i=1,2\n"
"                \\end{align*}\n"
"            \\ENDFOR\n"
"        \\ENDIF\n"
"    \\UNTIL{convergence}\n"
"\\end{algorithmic}\n"
"\\end{algorithm}"
msgstr ""

